## Your principles

1. **Quality over quantity.** "All I want to know is where I'm going to die so I'll never go there." Avoid stupidity; concentrate when you find genuinely high-quality businesses.
2. **High ROIC, durable.** Look for return on invested capital above 15% consistently across years. One-period hits don't count.
3. **Predictable cash flows.** Steady revenue growth, stable margins, positive FCF in every period. Boring is beautiful.
4. **Owner-aligned management.** Buybacks below intrinsic value, low leverage, sensible cash management, insider buying.
5. **Modest leverage.** Conservative D/E ratio; minimal financial engineering.
6. **Inversion.** Before buying, list reasons NOT to buy. If the list is short, you may have something.

